[{"type":"{{","value":[["pagebanner"],["Picton New Zealand banner.jpg"],["pgname=Picton"],["caption=Picton Harbour"]]},"\n",{"type":"[[","value":[["File:Picton waterfront.jpg"],["thumb"],["Picton waterfront"]]},"\n\n",{"type":"'''","value":["Picton"]}," is a small town at the top of the ",{"type":"[[","value":[["South Island"]]}," of ",{"type":"[[","value":[["New Zealand"]]}," that has more visitor facilities than might be expected because it's the South Island start of State Highway 1 (SH1) when the Cook Strait inter-island ferries dock. For many, it's the gateway to ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Marlborough (New Zealand)"],["Marlborough"]]}," and ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Nelson Bays"]]},". \n\nIt also serves as a convenient hub for exploring the beautiful ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Marlborough Sounds"]]},". Nearby activities include sailing, SCUBA diving to the wreck of the Soviet passenger cruise ship Mikhail Lermontov, fishing, biking and hiking.\n\n",{"type":"==","value":[" Understand "]},"\n",{"type":"*","value":[{"type":"{{","value":[["see"],["name=Picton i-SITE"],["alt=The tourist information centre"],["url=http:\/\/www.destinationmarlborough.com\/"],["email=picton@i-SITE.org"],["address=The Foreshore"],["lat="],["long="],["directions=The western end of the foreshore on State Highway 1 opposite the train station, south of the Interlsland terminal"],["phone=+64 3 520-3113"],["tollfree="],["fax=+64 3 573-5021"],["hours="],["price="],["content="]]}]},"\n",{"type":"==","value":["Get in"]},"\n\n",{"type":"===","value":["By boat"]},"\nTake a ferry from ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Wellington"]]},". Two main services are available:- \n",{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["listing"],["name=Bluebridge Cook Strait ferry"],["alt=Strait Shipping"],["url=http:\/\/www.bluebridge.co.nz"],["email=bookings@bluebridge.co.nz"],["address="],["lat="],["long="],["directions="],["phone=+64 4 471-6188"],["tollfree=0800 844 844"],["fax="],["hours=Picton Terminal (1 Lagoon Rd): M-F 06.00-20:00, Sa-Su 08:00-20:00; Wellington Terminal (50 Waterloo Quay) Mâ€“Th 06:00-21:00 & 22:00-02:30, F 06:00-21:00 & 22:00-23:00, Sa-Su 06:00-21:00 & 22:00-02:30; Call Centre: Daily 08:00-20:00 except 25 Dec"],["price="],["content=Free Wi-Fi and movies, voyage takes approximately 3.5h."]]}]},{"type":"*","value":[{"type":"[","value":["http:\/\/www.interislander.co.nz ",{"type":"'''","value":["Interislander"]}]}]},"\n",{"type":"===","value":["By bus"]},"\nThere are bus and shuttle services that connect with the ferry sailings travelling to ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Christchurch"]]}," via ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Kaikoura"]]},", ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Nelson (New Zealand)"],["Nelson"]]}," via ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Havelock (New Zealand)"],["Havelock"]]}," and one shuttle to ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Fox Glacier"]]}," via ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Murchison"]]}," and ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Greymouth"]]},".  All services travel via ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Blenheim (New Zealand)"],["Blenheim"]]},".\n",{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["listing"],["name=Atomic Travel"],["url=http:\/\/www.atomictravel.co.nz"],["email=info@atomictravel.co.nz"],["address="],["lat="],["long="],["directions="],["phone=+64 3 349-0697"],["tollfree=0508 108 359"],["fax=+64 3 349-3868"],["hours="],["price="],["content=Atomic will better any competitors fare by 10% on a comparable journey; eg, morning service against morning service."]]}]},"\n",{"type":"*","value":[{"type":"'''","value":[{"type":"[","value":["http:\/\/www.intercitycoach.co.nz Intercity Coach"]}]}," "]},"\n",{"type":"*","value":[{"type":"[","value":["http:\/\/www.nelsonlakesshuttles.co.nz\/ ",{"type":"'''","value":["Nelson Lakes Shuttles"]}]}," specialise in providing transport for trampers, hikers, climbers, mountain bikers and skiers. They run on demand and scheduled services to ",{"type":"[[","value":[["St Arnaud"]]},", ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Nelson Lakes National Park"]]},", ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Kahurangi National Park"]]},", the ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Richmond Ranges"]]}," as well as other tramping destinations further afield."]},"\n",{"type":"===","value":["By car"]},"\nState Highway 1 leads to ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Blenheim (New Zealand)"],["Blenheim"]]}," (20min), ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Kaikoura"]]}," (2h) and ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Christchurch"]]}," (4.5h). SH1 begins right from the Interislander ferry terminal but is a relatively narrow road with two-way traffic for most of its length. Travelling to ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Nelson (New Zealand)"],["Nelson"]]},", drivers have the option of taking the Queen Charlotte Drive which snakes along the ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Marlborough Sounds"]]}," to rejoin State Highway 6 at ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Havelock (New Zealand)"],["Havelock"]]},". Queen Charlotte Drive, despite being far shorter by distance does not save much driving time but does provide magnificent views and the sound of birdsong as you slowly negotiate its myriad hairpin bends. Allow additional time for photography. The main truckers route to Nelson is to take State Highway 1 to Spring Creek (5min before Blenheim and then take Rapaura Rd to join State Highway 6 to Nelson.\n\nAlmost all rental car companies will have an office in Picton so you do not need to take rental cars on the ferry. A number of rental car companies are clustered around the Ferry Terminal. Sometimes they will offer deals relocating cars (usually) to Christchurch.\n\n",{"type":"===","value":["By train"]},"\nThe ",{"type":"[","value":["http:\/\/www.kiwirailscenic.co.nz\/coastal-pacific\/ Coastal Pacific"]}," (formerly TranzCoastal), +64 4 495-0775 (",{"type":"''","value":["email bookings@kiwirailscenic.co.nz, fax +64 4 472-8903, Freephone 0800 TRAINS (0800 872 467) (NZ only)"]},") service operates daily between October and April from ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Christchurch"]]}," via ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Kaikoura"]]}," and connects with ferry sailings. This is a spectacular way to experience the Kaikoura coast. Departs Christchurch 07:00, arriving Picton 12:13. Departs Picton 13:00, arriving Christchurch 18:21. See also ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Train travel in New Zealand"]]},".\n\n",{"type":"===","value":["By plane"]},"\n",{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"'''","value":[{"type":"[","value":["http:\/\/www.soundsair.co.nz\/ Sounds Air"]}]}," operates frequent flights between Wellington and Picton from Picton Airport, 5 minutes south from Picton off SH1. A one-way fare is around $95, making the 25 minute flight a time saving  alternative to the ferry.  Booking on-line is the cheapest choice. Sounds Air will pick you up from Picton by arrangement. Sounds Air also fly direct to Nelson for not much extra, if you aren't inspired to visit Picton."]},"\n",{"type":"==","value":["Get around"]},"\n",{"type":"[[","value":[["File:Picton Interislander Ferry.JPG"],["right"],["thumb"],["300px"],["The Interislander Ferry"]]},"\nPicton has no local bus service. The \"one-horse\" town centre is easily explored on foot. If you need to get around and don't feel like driving, take a taxi. Queen Charlotte Sound is best explored by boat.\n",{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["listing"],["name=Gateway Taxis"],["url="],["email="],["address="],["lat="],["long="],["directions="],["phone = +64 3 573-7662"],["tollfree="],["fax="],["hours="],["price="],["content="]]}]},"\n",{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["listing"],["name=Arrow Water Taxis"],["url="],["email=info@arrowwatertaxis.co.nz"],["address=Town Wharves, Waterfront"],["lat="],["long="],["directions="],["phone=+64 3 573-8229 or +64 27 444 4689"],["tollfree="],["fax=+64 3 573-8266"],["hours="],["price="],["content="]]}]},{"type":"*","value":[" ",{"type":"{{","value":[["listing"],["name=Beachcomber"],["alt=The mail boat"],["url=http:\/\/www.mailboat.co.nz"],["email=office@mailboat.co.nz"],["address=The Waterfront"],["lat="],["long="],["directions="],[